title: Saint Joan (1957 History) The peasant girl who defied kings, armies, and the church.

sources.title: Saint Joan (1957 History) The peasant girl who defied kings, armies, and the church.
sources.description:
In 1456, French King Charles VII recalls the story of how he met the seventeen-year-old peasant girl Joan of Arc, entrusted her with the command of the French Army, and ultimately burned her at the stake as a heretic.

Original title: Saint Joan
Alternative title: Bernard Shaw's Saint Joan

Director: Otto Preminger
Writers: Graham Greene, George Bernard Shaw 

Main cast:
Jean Seberg - Joan of Arc
Richard Widmark - The Dauphin, later Charles VII
Richard Todd - Dunois, Bastard of Orl√©ans
Anton Walbrook - Peter Cauchon, Bishop of Beauvais
John Gielgud - Richard de Beauchamp, Earl of Warwick

Genres: Biography, Drama, Historical, Literary
Release date: May 8, 1957
Filming location: Shepperton Studios, London, England
